# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for the thriving-teams project
# =============================================================================
# Goal: protect confidential participant data and keep the repo tidy.
# Each block below explains *why* the patterns are excluded, so future
# contributors can adjust with confidence.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Confidential data (highest priority)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Raw SPSS files, R serialised objects and any CSVs holding identifiable or
# participant-level data must never enter version control. The README states
# that data_raw/ is "not tracked publicly" — this enforces that promise.
data_raw/
data_processed/
*.sav
*.zsav
*.por
*.rds
*.RData
*.rdata
*.RDS
*.feather
*.parquet

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated outputs
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tables, figures and logs are regenerated on demand by the scripts; keeping
# them out of git avoids review noise and prevents stale artefacts from being
# treated as authoritative.
output/
figures/
logs/
*.csv
*.tsv
*.xlsx
*.xls
!scripts/_smoke_data/*.csv      # allow the synthetic fixture if added later
!*.example.csv                  # allow worked-example fixtures

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Credentials and environment
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never commit secrets or environment-specific paths.
.Renviron
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# R session and history files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These capture personal R sessions and are not reproducible artefacts.
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history
.Rproj.user/
.Ruserdata

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RStudio project metadata
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Keep the top-level .Rproj file (tracked) so collaborators can open the
# project, but ignore the per-user state directory.
.Rproj.user/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# renv package cache (lockfile is committed; library is not)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When renv is added, the lockfile (renv.lock) and the activate script
# (renv/activate.R) are committed; the local library is regenerated by
# renv::restore() and must stay out of git.
renv/library/
renv/local/
renv/cellar/
renv/lock/
renv/python/
renv/staging/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build artefacts and caches
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.Rcheck/
*.tar.gz
*.html
*_cache/
*_files/
/cache/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LaTeX intermediates (if Sweave/knitr/Quarto outputs land here)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.aux
*.log
*.toc
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.out

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Operating system files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor and IDE local files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python (in case ancillary tooling is added)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
